Storages.
    - AngularJS Supports the Following Types Of Storages.
        1.localStorage
        2.sessionStorage

    - localStorage.
            - localStorage will be deleted by user explicitely.

    - sessionStorage.
            - when ever we close the browser , automatically we will lost the data
              from sessionStorage.

    - "ngStorage" is the predefined module, used to work with the Storages.

    - "ngStorage" will provide following Objects.
      - $localStorage
      - $sessionStorage

    - $localStorage used to work with the localStorage.

    - $sessionStorage used to work with the sessionStorage.

    - we can Store the Data in the form of "key&value" pairs.

